# llm-docs.nvim

A Neovim plugin to browse and read documentation from projects that provide an `llms.txt` file. Powered by `curl.nvim` and `telescope.nvim`.

## 🚀 Features
- **Remote Fetching**: Uses `curl.nvim` for asynchronous fetching (no UI freeze).
- **Multi-Project Support**: Configure as many `llms.txt` sources as you want.
- **Instant Access**: Opens documentation in a formatted Markdown scratch buffer.
- **Searchable**: Leverages Telescope for fuzzy finding through document titles.

## 📦 Installation

Using [lazy.nvim](https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim):

```lua
{
  "atomicwerks/llm-docs.nvim",
  dependencies = {
    "oysandvik94/curl.nvim",
    "nvim-telescope/telescope.nvim",
    "nvim-lua/plenary.nvim",
  },
  -- This automatically calls require("llm-docs").setup(opts)
  opts = {
    projects = {
      {
        name = "Vendure",
        url = "https://docs.vendure.io/llms.txt",
        base_url = "https://docs.vendure.io",
      },
      {
        name = "OpenAI",
        url = "https://platform.openai.com/llms.txt",
        base_url = "https://platform.openai.com",
      },
    },
  },
  cmd = "LLMDocs", -- Lazy-load only when the command is run
  keys = {
    { "<leader>ld", "<cmd>LLMDocs<cr>", desc = "Browse LLM Docs" },
  },
}
